Questions are being asked about how self-proclaimed prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, managed to escape South Africa. A warrant for their arrest has been issued. Tshegohaco Moagi has more on the story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Shepherd and Mary Bushiri have been warned to appear in the Pretoria Magistrate's Court on Thursday or risk losing their R5.5-million property in Centurion. A warrant has been issued for their arrest after they fled the country while out on bail. READ: SA breaks silence on fugitive Bushiri eNCA also understands that their bail has been revoked. The church leader and his wife face charges of fraud and money laundering. READ: Cele: Bushiris shouldn't have been granted bail In a video on social media, Bushiri says they felt unsafe in South Africa. He is demanding that the government assure their protection before they will return.